# FORE — environment variables

## Core (always)

```bash
RENDER_ML_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8000
GROQ_API_KEY=
GROQ_MODEL=llama-3.1-8b-instant
ALLOWED_ORIGINS=   # Render ML service — comma-separated Vercel domains
```

## Full-stack mode (FORE Blueprint 2 — JWT + PostgreSQL)

When `DATABASE_URL` is set, auth middleware activates and real bank CSV upload is available.

```bash
# PostgreSQL (Neon, Supabase, Railway, etc.)
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://USER:PASSWORD@HOST:5432/fore?sslmode=require

# JWT signing secret (long random string, min 32 chars)
JWT_ACCESS_SECRET=

# AES-256 key for encrypting transaction descriptions at rest
# Generate: openssl rand -base64 32
DATA_ENCRYPTION_KEY=
```

### Setup

```bash
npm install
npx prisma generate
npx prisma db push    # or: npx prisma migrate dev
npm run dev
```

Register at `/register`, upload bank CSV on PAST, or use demo personas.

See [docs/SECURITY.md](docs/SECURITY.md) for how real bank data is protected.
